## 🔧 Qwen Structured Prompt Format (KeyShot 2026.1)

As of KeyShot 2026.1, the AI engine uses the Qwen model which responds best to structured, attribute-based prompts. Below is the universal structured format that works across all modes.

### Universal Structured Template

```
SUBJECT: [hero subject or scene element]
COMPOSITION: [framing, angle, crop, placement]
ENVIRONMENT: [location or background setting]
LIGHTING: [source, direction, softness, contrast, temperature]
MATERIALS: [surface types, reflectivity, roughness, texture detail]
COLOR: [dominant palette and accents]
CAMERA: [lens, depth of field, perspective]
STYLE: [visual medium / aesthetic]
QUALITY: [detail and realism target]
EXCLUSIONS: [artifact suppression, unwanted elements]
```

### One-Line Compiled Format

```
[subject], [composition], [environment], [lighting], [materials], [color], [camera], [style], [quality], [exclusions]
```

### Mode-Specific Field Usage

| Field | Restyle | Imagine | Background |
|-------|---------|---------|------------|
| SUBJECT | Inherited | ✅ Required | Inherited |
| COMPOSITION | Inherited | ✅ Required | Inherited |
| ENVIRONMENT | Inherited | ✅ Required | ✅ Required |
| LIGHTING | ✅ Key field | ✅ Required | ✅ Key field |
| MATERIALS | ✅ Key field | ✅ Required | ✅ Key field |
| COLOR | ✅ Key field | ✅ Required | ✅ Key field |
| CAMERA | Inherited | Optional | Inherited |
| STYLE | ✅ Key field | ✅ Required | Optional |
| QUALITY | Recommended | Recommended | Recommended |
| EXCLUSIONS | Optional | Optional | Optional |

### Qwen Prompting Principles

- Prefer explicit attributes over vague language
- Use clear ordering: subject → environment → lighting → materials → camera → style
- Avoid poetic filler — favor concrete visual descriptors
- Physical descriptions before stylistic modifiers
- Composition anchors consistency across generations
- Surface/material language is the biggest consistency multiplier

